
St.John Baptist de La Salle

1.Founder of Institute of the Brothers of the Christian Schools
2.Patron Saint of Teachers
3.Born in Reims,France
4.Canon of Rheims Cathedral at fifteen
5.He became a priesthood at the age of 26 on April 9, 1678
6.Dedicated to educate the poor children in France
7.He was born to a wealthy family
8.He gave up his wealth and his position as canon to live with teachers
9.At the age of 67, he died on the 7th day of April 1719
10.Canonized by Pope Leo XIII